!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

problem /ˈprɒbləm/

(problems) 

1. N-COUNT A problem is a situation that is unsatisfactory and causes difficulties for people. 问题 

例： ...the economic problems of the inner city. …内城的经济问题。 

例： I do not have a simple solution to the drug problem. 我并没有一个简单的解决毒品问题的方法。 

2. N-COUNT A problem is a puzzle that requires logical thought or mathematics to solve it. 题目 

例： With mathematical problems, you can save time by approximating. 对于数学题，你可以用近似法省时间。

</div>

